Actually, I'd say the normal -10 modifier that Wizard spells should be adequate, not the -50 modifer. The reason for this is the one you mentioned in your post: Mages get Malosinia. I don't see why they shouldn't be required to cast this if there is a problem getting spells to land, as that is the reason they have the spell. Giving them the -50 Draughts would, in this case, make them better than a normal Wizard because they don't get the option to do Malosinia on top of the normal resist debuff built into the spells. Given that the pets do not have to worry about a mana pool, I feel it is a more than fair trade off to require the Mage to actually use his spells occasionally. <p><!--EZCODE LINK START--><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=4380">Qaman</a><!--EZCODE LINK END--><br>
