<!--EZCODE LINK START--><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=448514">Antrygus Windrose </a><!--EZCODE LINK END--> </p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#33333><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub140.ezboard.com/bgraffeswizardcompilation.showUserPublicProfile?gid=rhasinfirestorm>rhasinfirestorm</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Visitor</span><br>  Posts: 4<br> <font color=#ffffff>(6/6/03 3:17 pm)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: *FACTS* on new mage pets</span><hr size=1> Faramir,<br>
<br>
It is my thought that SoE's 'testing' was &quot;raising the effective casting level&quot; only, not clearly defining a new set of spells. What they hoped to accomplish by this, I haven't a clue, unless they had deemed the NPC made to be the fire pets garbage, scrapped them, and remade them under new tools. Also, the last I heard from our illustrious Magician Board leader, SoE devs were discussing quite heatedly over the specific spells to include or exclude from the spell lineup. SoE knows there's an issue with the spells.<br>
<br>
As with the name calling (mages doing it, the few wizards that were doing it), I wholeheartedly concur. Those mages that said they were going to laugh, well I'd be more than eager to laugh at them when the resulting changes to the fire pet does not make it a godpet, and even goes live sans root and snare (I do not believe those are going live. Snare for sure won't, and I pray root is not included). While I think the backlash from magicians at the wizards saying 'IC is too much' (which it is) is, as you said, fear of the pet being relegated to garbage once again, something no mage wants to happen. We also have our share of naysayers that chant how the fire pet will never be upgraded and how they were quitting when SoE's 'next update' page came out without a mention of the upgrades to the fire pet. Good riddance to him.<br>
<br>
Point that I was getting at, I guess, is that those few (many?) mages married to IC and/or Snare should be ignored (they're likely stubborn and won't accept reason). They're idiots and they deserve to be let down if they can't think about the bigger picture. What aught to happen is a discussion of what spells are good, and what (paired with a mage's own abilities) would be appropriate.<br>
<br>
Kinda like.. With a slight investment of mana, all Fire pet spells are effectively lure (Mala = -35 unresistable debuff to any spell the fire pet would cast). Fire pets may already have an innate ability to land spells, being NPC's (and therefor, may not need too much help). The fire pet is a level 60 caster, and with the top level being 65, mobs that a caster can land spells on can most likely be hit by a level 60 pet. Only when the difference in pet level to NPC level reaches 14 levels or more will the pet be completely incapable of landing spells (Magician epic pet is level 49. It unequivocably cannot proc or land it's stun on mobs that are level 63 and higher). Are there any mobs in game that are level 74 or higher?<br>
